description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Advanced Nurse Practitioner within the Scarborough, Whitby &amp; Ryedale Crisis and Home Treatment team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be a Registered Mental Health Nurse with considerable community experience. The applicant should also hold Independent prescribing qualification or demonstrate a willingness to work towards this qualification within a specified timeframe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be an active part of the Crisis and Home Treatment supercell offering leadership and guidance to the wider team. You will be involved in all service development work within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additionally you would be responsible for the clinical supervision of Senior Community Mental Health Nurses within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A thorough understanding of the Mental Health Act, Mental Capacity Act and Human Rights Act will be essential to the role as these will provide the framework for all consideration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be required to contribute to the Senior Nurse On call rota (SNOC) as part of their job role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Cory, Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;emma.cory@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
